	)
	(text "Components to wire in KiCad (placed unwired here):\n  U1        TMC2130-LA\n  RSA, RSB  0.1 ohm 1210 (sense, standard variant)\n  RSA_M, RSB_M   0.68 ohm 1210 DNP (sense, micro variant)\n  C_VS_BULK 10 uF 50V 1210 (motor supply bulk near VS pins 16+31)\n  C_VS      100 nF 0402 (VS HF bypass)\n  C_VSA     100 nF 0402 (VSA filter, pin 30)\n  C_CP      22 nF 50V 0402 (CPH<->CPL charge pump flying cap)\n  C_VCP     100 nF 50V 0402 (VCP->VS charge pump storage)\n  C_5VOUT   2.2 uF 6.3V 0603 (5VOUT->GNDA internal LDO)\n  C_VCC     100 nF 0402 (VCC->GND digital supply)\n  C_AIN     100 nF 0402 (AIN_IREF->GNDA reference filter)\n  R_DIAG1   47 k 0402 pull-up to +3V3 on DIAG1"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 110 20 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "1d912666-0f32-4d96-b735-7666b5f14159")
	)
	(text "ONE TMC2130 STEPPER CHANNEL\n\nThis sheet represents a single channel of TMC2130 motor driving with\nall the per-driver support passives from the datasheet.\n\nInstantiate this sheet twice on the ministepper root — KiCad auto-\nrenumbers refs per instance (U1->U1/U2, C1->C1/C13, R1->R1/R8, etc.).\n\nHierarchical ports:\n  SCK, MOSI, MISO, DRV_ENN  - shared SPI bus + shared enable\n  CS, STEP, DIR, DIAG1      - per-channel signals\n  MOT_A+/-, MOT_B+/-        - bipolar motor phases to JMOTx\n\nGlobal power nets (no port needed, use power symbols):\n  +3V3  (logic / VCC_IO)\n  VPP   (motor supply, 5-37V)\n  GND"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 15 20 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "2d0bb7f8-ee6c-4949-bdcb-aba6c147329a")
	)
	(text "Sense-resistor variants (assembly-time choice):\n  STANDARD populated: RSA/RSB = 0.1 ohm 1210 (NEMA17-class, up to 1.5A RMS)\n  MICRO populated:    RSA_M/RSB_M = 0.68 ohm 1210 (50-200mA, 28BYJ-48)\n\nOnly ONE pair should be populated at a time. The micro variant requires\nthe firmware to set CHOPCONF.VSENSE=1 (see firmware/tsumikoro-ministepper).\n\nStrapping (firmware-agnostic, tied via power symbols inside this sheet):\n  CLK (pin 1)        -> GND (use internal 12 MHz oscillator)\n  SPI_MODE (pin 10)  -> +3V3 (hardware SPI mode)\n  TST_MODE (pin 36)  -> GND\n  DCEN (pin 18), DCIN (pin 19) -> GND (dcStep disabled)\n  DNC (pin 9), N.C. (pin 11)   -> open"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 15 70 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "61a42839-8b8d-453c-b3bc-653a7bcb1035")
	)
